attributes.title: Young's Seafood's langoustines: former organization.
attributes.description: The British firm Young’s Seafood has been catching langoustines in the Scotland Sea for decades. Until now, these langoustines were mechanically peeled in local units, and sold in British chains of stores, such as Marks and Spencer.
